## Performance & quality bar
- Lighthouse > 90 on mobile for Home
- Avoid heavy client JS: server components by default, client only where needed (tabs, modal, search input).
- Use caching (Next fetch cache) and pagination.
- Validate forms server-side.
- No hardcoded strings; use i18n keys.

## Coding style
- Small components, clear props types.
- Prefer server actions (or API routes) for form submit.
- Provide seed scripts for demo data.
- Write minimal tests for critical utils.

## Deliverables per task
When implementing a feature:
1) Update routes
2) Add/modify DB schema (if needed)
3) Implement UI components
4) Wire data + error states + loading skeletons
5) Add i18n keys
6) Document how to run locally

## Acceptance criteria
- Home looks and behaves like the reference layout (structure/sections), but with original branding/content.
- Category navigation works; product detail works; news works; catalogue lead captured.
